<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-276-308  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 276 308.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  May 16 1989 v3 n20 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dow Jones adds front end. (Dow Jones and Co. Inc.'s E-Z Onlinesoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brower, Emily.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dow Jones and Company Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   E-Z Online (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionInformation ServicesData BasesFinancial Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Dow Jones adds front endandM;Princeton, N.J.andP;  -- New software offered by Dow Jones as a front end to itsNews/Retrieval on-line business news and information network may mark asignificant step toward personalized electronic newspapers.andM;The program, called E-Z Online, gives News/Retrieval subscribers automaticlog-on and information retrieval from Dow Jones' news and informationdatabases, which cover not only business and financial developments, but alsonational and international news, sports, weather and movie reviews.andM;Users create their personalized news report plans off-line.andP;  Once the topicsof interest have been selected, E-Z Online logs on and retrieves theinformation without any user interaction.andP;  Multiple report forms can be savedunder their own names.andM;For example, in the company and stock price section, a user can choose to getthe latest quotes and news on Apple or Sun Microsystems by simply enteringthose companies' stock symbols in a dialog box.andM;Retrieved information can be viewed on-line during the session or printedfrom the reports that are automatically saved to disk by the program.andM;Another E-Z Online program, the company report, lets users take a moredetailed look at a specific company, including not only stock prices, companynews and earnings estimates, but also industry comparisons, investmentresearch reports, financial data and even insider trading records.andP;  Theinformation comes from Dow Jones' QuickSearch, a service that gathers companyinformation from several other News/Retrieval databases.andM;E-Z Online also offers an interactive mode, allowing users to navigatethrough the Dow Jones databases on their own after an automatic log on.andM;The program was written with Acknowledge, a telecommunications developmentpackage previously published by SuperMac Technology and Lamir Software Corp.andO;but recently taken over by Prometheus.andP;  E-Z Online is the first commercialapplication to be produced with Acknowledge.andM;Dow Jones will start distributing the software in June with its MembershipsKits, which sell for $29.95 through software retailers.andM;Dow Jones andamp; Co. Inc. can be reached at P.O. Box 300, Princeton, N.J.andO;08543-0300; (609) 452-1511; (800) 522-3567.andO;</TEXT></DOC>